-- Summit's `Twilight' Ticket Sales Total $121.3 Million Since June 30 Debut
-- Dan Hart
-- 2010-07-03T16:22:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/summit-s-twilight-ticket-sales-total-121-3-million-since-june-30-debut.html

          
          
             “The Twilight Saga: Eclipse,” the
third film in Summit Entertainment LLC’s teen-vampire series,
had sales of $121.3 million in U.S. and Canadian theaters since
its June 30 debut.  
 “Eclipse” had receipts of $28.6 million yesterday,
following a record of more than $30 million from midnight
showings on June 30, box-office tracker Hollywood.com Box-Office
said today in an e-mail.  
 The movie took in a total of $68.5 million on June 30, and
$24.2 million on July 1, the researcher said.  
          
          


  


        